cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on hate-speech detection on social network language using machine learning and deep learning techniques. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with social network comments and their impact on online users. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper compares traditional machine learning models with neural network models for hate speech detection. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the negative impact of hate speech on online users. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the classification of user comments on social networks.
